===Etymology===
From {{etyl|frm}} {{term|pole||hen|lang=frm}} {{compound||cat}}. So named because of its fondness for poultry.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈpɑlkæt/}}
* {{IPA|/ˈpəʊlkæt/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[weasel]]-like animal of the genus ''[[Mustela]]'', notably the [[European polecat]], {{taxlink|Mustela putorius|species}}.
# {{US|dialect}} A [[skunk]].

====Quotations====
* '''1919,''' [[w:Ronald Firbank|Ronald Firbank]], ''[[w:Valmouth|Valmouth]]'', Duckworth, hardback edition, page 61
*: By the little garden pergola open to the winds some fluttered peacocks were blotted nervelessly amid the dripping trees, their heads sunk back beneath their wings: while in the pergoda itself, like a fallen storm-cloud, lolled a negress, her levelled, '''polecat''' eyes semi-veiled by the nebulous alchemy of the rainbow.

